            "weighted_score": 0.5801041126251221,
            "steam_purchase": true,
            "review_text": "Liked this software from the start icl. I got it mainly to mess around with friends in calls and games, but somehow it’s ended up being my most played “game” on Steam with 778.8 hours 💀\r\n\r\nI connected it to my Fifine AmpliGame stream deck and it works really well. Having sounds on actual buttons instead of tabbing out or searching for stuff makes it so much easier, especially when I’m in a game or Discord call.\r\n\r\nSoundpad itself is simple once you set it up. The hotkeys work well, playing sounds through the mic is smooth, and the quality is good as long as the sound files you use are decent.\r\n\r\nMain reason I use it is just for funny moments with friends. Being able to instantly play random sounds at the right time is honestly so convenient.\r\n\r\nOnly small thing is the UI looks a bit old, but it does the job and I’d rather have that than some flashy app that barely works.\r\n\r\nNever thought a soundboard would be my most played thing on Steam but yeah... Soundpad is worth it."
        },
